node.text:
When I was 30, I got my dream job. And within two weeks of having it, the corners of my mouth started to crack. 

I was stressed. 
Exhausted. 
Waking up at 4am and sleeping at midnight and spending my weekends in the office, my life in the office. 

And my body, it was trying so hard to tell me something so simple:
Slow down. 
Breathe, darling. 
Breath before you break. 

From my Facebook group, I know I’m not the only one who does this:
Who loads the stress on,
And adds weight to an already full burden. 
Saying yes when we should say no,
And feeling a responsibility to keep going,
A shame if we stop. 

If this sounds like you,
Know this:

Your mental health matters. 
In all the ways, in all the situations, it matters. 

Balance is so critical to living this life, this ONE life, that we’ve got. 
And waking up covered in sweat,
Or skipping all things social just to keep on pushing,
That’s not healthy. 

So today, give yourself grace 
To look at your life, your goals,
And lean in to what is TRULY right for you. 

Even if it means stepping back from that project,
Or skipping that promotion,
Or cancelling on those birthday plans. 

It took me a year to hear what my body and my heart were trying to tell me.

Don’t let it take you a minute more.

node.text:
We have to talk about periods. Honestly. Openly. Without shame.

Because if we don’t, 
Stupidity like this holds power. 

For years, for MANY years, I was ignorant about my period. 

I lost it, when I became overly thin. 
Then I went on birth control that kept it away. 

It wasn’t until I hit my 30s that I started looking in to how my period worked. 
How it ACTUALLY worked, beyond the soft delicacy we are taught about blue dye on white cotton pads. 

I downloaded a free period tracker,
And for the first time ever, 
Started to tap into the power of my cycle. 

Now I feel increasingly strong about fighting idiocy like this. 
Because these men, who perhaps have been told almost nothing about periods their whole lives,
Are often the ones making decisions that impact ours. 

So it’s time we talked. 
Without shame. 
Without embarrassment. 
To each other. 
And to them too. 
Owning with each word, each conversation, 
The marvel that is our body. 

Period. 

x

#selflove #feminist #periods

By the time you are 17, you’ll have seen over 20,000 ads telling you what beauty looks like. 

It’s no surprise that by 14, one in every three girls is unhappy with her body. 

And that number? 
It shoots up to 91% by the time we’re adults. 

So in this environment,
In this space,
It’s no surprise that self love is hard. 

That we have good days 
And bad days. 

Moments when we feel strong in our skin,
And seconds where old habits or ugly thoughts creep in. 

But all that’s ok. 
Because what matters is we are TRYING. 

We are taking steps in a direction that serves us;

One where we see our bodies not as enemies,
But as homes. 

One where we don’t obsess over shrinking, 
But focus on how our joy can grow. 

One where we push back against the nonsense
That we have been fed for so long. 

That path is a powerful one,
A worthy one,
A brave one. 

Because it can change how we feel about ourselves today. 

And how our littles feels about themselves tomorrow. 

#selflove #bodyconfidence #bodyacceptance #bodyimage

node.text:
We lost our wedding venue this week. 

The owners had to cancel. 
Now we have less than 24 days to find a new one. 

It’s been a bit stressful.
The uncertainty, the upheaval. 
The re-searching for reception venues when we should be tasting cakes and picking plates. 

But in the same breath, 
It feels ok. 

Because for me,
For us, 
The wedding day is a wonderful thing. 
But the marriage — the months, the years, the union -- THAT’s what really matters. 

So today, 
For anyone dangling in their own bit of stress,
I just want to remind you: 

Step back. 
Breathe deeply. 
And remember this moment too will pass. 
Life is like that, always ebbing and flowing. 
And the tiny blips, the uncomfortable hiccups,
They don’t stick around for long. 

Us humans, we are strong. 
YOU are strong. 
And far greater goals drive us, 
Than the momentary setbacks that cross our paths. 

So here’s to you. 
To us. 

To lives full of love.
Wherever they might lead.

x

Picture by @indie.marea 

#selflove #weddings #weddingdates #lovequotes

I don’t battle food anymore. I did, for years I did. 

But now, in this house, in this body, we don’t play that game. 

A huge shift occurred for me when I stopped seeing FOOD as the enemy,

And started looking at it as FUEL. 

Fuel for my body, 
To help drive towards any goals I have:
Run faster. Lift heavier. 
Feel stronger. 

But also fuel for my soul. 

Sometimes that means eating grandma’s cake. 
Or having a cookie baked by a love one. 
Or diving in to a plate of pasta, made by a man you’re about to marry. 

And that’s wonderful too. 

So today, I just want to gently remind you:
Your body is not a battle ground,
And eating isn’t the enemy. 

You deserve to feel nourished,
Both in your body,
And in your soul. 

x

Kit @womensbest @womensbestwear 

#womensbestathlete #bodyconfidence #selflove #bodyacceptance

I intended this to be a light-hearted post. A playful, tongue-in-cheek skit looking at introverts and parties. 

But the post had other ideas. 

To this day, I’m still a little self conscious about being an introvert. 
I feel shy that I DON’T like parties, that I never really have.
I’m embarrassed that giant crowds, thumping night clubs, those aren’t my idea of fun. 

I struggle with it, in my own little, soft way. 

And I figure if I’m still learning to navigate being introverted in an extroverted world, 
Or even being true to myself, in a world that tries to tell us otherwise,
Maybe you are too.

So today, I want to remind me and you and us:

It is ok to lean into what ACTUALLY brings you joy,
And pull away from things that don’t. 

You do not HAVE to go to that frat party,
Or that loud club,
Or that event full of people which will leave you feeling empty. 

It is absolutely fine to slide into quiet spaces: 
Bookstores, cafes, mornings on the beach with the closest of friends. 

Or just to find your people where YOU yourself like to be. 

For me, that has been at the gym, in sports, and in art. 
For you, that might be a dozen other places. And that’s ok. 

Wherever you go, make sure you go in a way that is TRUE to you. 

You don’t have to change a thing about yourself. 
Just change the things around you. 

Because life is too short to hide in bathrooms,
And you — introverted or extroverted, noisy or loud, passionate or shy — are glorious just the way you are.

x

#introverts #selflove #bodyconfidence #introverted

This app edits BODIES in VIDEOS - and trust me, technology like this is only becoming more common. 

In a matter of seconds, I was able to:
Enhance my bust
Get a bigger bum 
Lift my thighs 
Shrink my tummy 
And so much more. 

If I wanted to, I could have also made my legs longer, filtered my face and done a dozen other things. 

And it was SO EASY to do. 

Technology like this is popping up more and more. It’s all the big screen Hollywood tools, brought to your phone. 

And it’s constantly getting SMARTER. Like this app includes an option to BLUR the background, so that you don’t see WHERE the edits have happened. 

So please, the next time you start to compare yourself to what you see on here, remember that the INTERNET is CURATED. 
Filtered. 
Posed. 
Aaaand sometimes even assisted with a body photoshopping video app. 

In other words, your offline self doing great. 

x

#instavsreality #videoediting #bodyconfidence #selflove

node.text:
There will always be someone who cannot see your worth. 

Just make sure that person is not you. 

Because you, my dear,
You are enough. 

You always have been. 

Even if your energy is not theirs. 
Even if your body comes in a different shape,
Or your smile in its own form. 

These things don’t make you less than. 
They don’t mean you’re lacking. 

They’re just parts and pieces 
Of the marvel, the magic that you are. 

And if they cannot see it, 
That is ok;
People all vibrate to their own rhythm. 

But it doesn’t mean you have to listen. 

The voice that matters is your own. 

So today and tomorrow and every day,
Remind yourself:
You, you glorious complex creature,
You marvellous woman,
However you choose to show up, however you choose to be you,
You are enough. 

You. Are. Enough. 

x

Image inspired by @cydneylrj 

#selflove #bodyconfidence #bodyacceptance #positivequotes

node.text:
I can’t wait to be back home. 

Three years ago, I wouldn’t have really understood this sentiment. 

Home was never something I had growing up. 
And as an adult, as a travel journalist living around the world, it never really came into play. 

But when I adopted Kiki cat, things started to change. 
With Koala kitten, they shifted even more. 
They brought peace. Laughter. 
A reason to feel impatient getting back to that front door. 

And now there’s him:
The voice on the other end of the line. 
The messages sent down a phone. 
‘What are you doing now?’ And ‘what did you eat today?’ And ‘make sure you don’t leave the kitties alone.’ 

Somewhere between the first four paws and this Italian fiancée, a piece inside me changed. 

House became home. 
And I can’t wait to get back to mine. 

x
